medical_history.history_of_present_illness: Abdominal pain developed suddenly 15 hours before evaluation after eating breakfast. The pain was sharp, constant, and rated 8 out of 10, more severe than during previous deliveries. Pain did not improve with oral docusate and slightly decreased after taking acetaminophen. Nausea developed after the pain persisted.
medical_history.past_medical_history: Pregnant at 36 weeks 3 days of gestation; previous uncomplicated vaginal deliveries, one spontaneous abortion; breast augmentation and wisdom tooth extraction surgeries.
medical_history.family_history: Father died of liver disease associated with alcohol use disorder; mother had cervical cancer and hypertension, died of a ruptured cerebral aneurysm.
medical_history.social_history: Lives with husband and two children; does not drink alcohol, smoke tobacco, or use illicit drugs.
